# Important File Locations

## Core Logic

### src/orchestrator/

Core validation and execution logic:

- `orchestrator.ts` - Main orchestration loop (refactored into subsystems)
- `turn-manager.ts` - Turn advancement and ownership validation
- `board-effects-handler.ts` - Board moves and square effects
- `decision-point-enforcer.ts` - Decision point requirements
- `validator.ts` - Primitive action validation entry (validateActions)
- `validator/` - Validation submodules (types, mock-state, common, narrate-reset, player-answered, player-rolled, riddle, set-state, square-effect)
- `types.ts` - Type definitions for primitives
- `name-collector.ts` - Voice-based player name collection

Supporting modules:

- `action-executors.ts` - Executes NARRATE, PLAYER_ROLLED, SET_STATE, etc.
- `board-traversal.ts` - Position computation for board moves
- `decision-helpers.ts` - Decision point lookup helpers
- `decision-point-inference.ts` - Infers decision points from game config
- `riddle-answer.ts` - Riddle answer resolution and validation
- `riddle-power-check.ts` - Power check / revenge phase handling
- `reorder-power-check.ts` - Power check reordering logic
- `square-types.ts` - Square kind utilities
- `validation-i18n.ts` - Validation error i18n keys

### src/llm/

LLM clients and system prompts:

- `LLMClient.ts` - Interface for LLM providers
- `BaseLLMClient.ts` - Base client with streaming, extended by providers
- `llm-client-factory.ts` - Creates client from CONFIG.LLM_PROVIDER
- `system-prompt.ts` - LLM system prompt generator
- `state-context.ts` - Formats game state for LLM context
- `parse-openai-response.ts` - Parses OpenAI-compatible responses (Groq, DeepInfra, OpenRouter)
- `GeminiClient.ts` - Google Gemini integration
- `OllamaClient.ts` - Local Ollama integration
- `GroqClient.ts` - Groq API integration
- `OpenRouterClient.ts` - OpenRouter API integration
- `DeepInfraClient.ts` - DeepInfra API integration
- `MockLLMClient.ts` - Test/mock client

## Services

### src/services/

Speech and UI services:

- `speech-service.ts` - TTS and audio playback
- `ui-service.ts` - UI service interface
- `production-ui-service.ts` - Minimal pulsating orb UI
- `debug-ui-service.ts` - Full debug console UI

## Audio Pipeline

### src/audio-worklet/

Audio processing for Vosk:

- `vosk-processor.js` - AudioWorklet processor

### src/voice-recognition/

Vosk STT pipeline:

- `wake-word.ts` - Wake word detection state machine
- `wake-word-utils.ts` - Wake word matching utilities
- `model-manager.ts` - Vosk model downloading and caching

## Game System

### src/game-loader/

Game definition loading (no barrel; import from `game-loader.ts` and `types.ts` directly):

- `game-loader.ts` - Loads game JSON and sound effects
- `types.ts` - Game definition types

### public/games/

Game definitions (JSON files):

- Each game has a directory with `config.json`
- Contains: metadata (id, name, objective, min/maxPlayers), squares, soundEffects (optional)

## State Management

- `src/state-manager.ts` - In-memory state manager with path-based operations

## Internationalization

### src/i18n/

- `translations.ts` - Translation functions (t, setLocale, getNicknames, etc.)
- `locale-manager.ts` - Locale persistence and selection (getLocale, getTtsLang)
- `riddle-judge-prompt.ts` - LLM prompt builder for fuzzy riddle answer grading (locale-aware; Spanish-first)
- `locales/` - Locale files (en-US, es-AR)

## Utilities

### src/utils/

Helper functions:

- `logger.ts` - Logging utility
- `profiler.ts` - Performance profiling
- `name-helper.ts` - Name transcription error correction

## Configuration & Entry Points

- `src/config.ts` - App configuration (wake word, timeouts, etc.)
- `src/main.ts` - Production app entry point
- `src/debug.ts` - Debug interface entry point

